<font color="#FF0000">TRADIONAL MEMORIAL DAY</font><br>
<tt>Sun May 25 12:51:51 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Let's return Memorial Day to May 30th for a tradional celebration instead of a day off for government offices and the 3-day start of summer holiday. This day was set aside to honor fallen vets of the Civil War and should return to that celebration.<br>
I like the idea of a national moment of silence but, again, believe it would better serve the vets if it was done on Memorial Day.
